Write a program to find whether the given string is a palindrome or not

Input Format

Read a string

Constraints

string

Output Format

If the given string is a Palindrome display “Palindrome”, else display “Not a Palindrome”.

Sample Input 0

madam
Sample Output 0

Palindrome
Sample Input 1

java
Sample Output 1

Not a Palindrome
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() 
{
    char str[100];  
  int i,n,comp=0;
   scanf("%s",str);
   n=strlen(str);
    for(i=0;i<n/2;i++)
    {
        if(str[1]==str[n-1-1])
            comp++;
    }
  if(comp==i)
  printf("Palindrome");
    else
  printf("Not a Palindrome");
  return 0;
}
